# Per-package license overrides for the dependency license check.
#
# go-licenses can't always classify a module's LICENSE file and reports
# "Unknown". When the license is in fact one of the allowed types (see
# .allowed-licenses), record it here so the check uses the real license
# instead of the undetected value. Format: one "module-path SPDX" pair per
# line; comments start with #.
#
# The override applies to the module path and everything under it.

# segmentio/asm ships under MIT-0 ("MIT No Attribution"): the standard MIT
# text minus the attribution clause, so strictly more permissive. The
# license classifier go-licenses uses can't match the clause-trimmed text
# and reports Unknown; MIT-0 is in .allowed-licenses.
# https://github.com/segmentio/asm/blob/main/LICENSE
github.com/segmentio/asm MIT-0
